tweet_text: @PhilMacDonald14 @JournalStarNews Money is fungible.  Schools in Nebraska (especially outside of Omaha) receive virtually no funding from the state government.  If property taxes were not funding schools, the state would have to be.  Thus, property taxes equal money in the state's pocket one way or the other.
